# NET
.NET is a general purpose development platform. It has several key features, such as support for multiple programming languages, asynchronous and concurrent programming models, and native interoperability, which enable a wide range of scenarios across multiple platforms.

+ .NET Basic Compoent - Mermaid Diagram Code
```mermaid
%%{init: {'theme':'base'}}%%
graph TB
  netac[.NET architectural components] --> netstd[.NET Standard]
  netac --> netimp-basic[Basic Components] 
  netstd --> overview>.NET Standard is a set of APIs that are implemented by the Base Class Library of a .NET implementation]
  netimp-basic --> |Mandatory|net-runtime[Runtime]
  netimp-basic --> |Mandatory|net-clslib[Class Library]
  netimp-basic --> |Optionally|net-appframework[Application Frameworks]
  netimp-basic --> |Optionally|net-devtools[Development Tools]
  net-runtime --> clr-netframework[CLR for .NET Framework]
  net-runtime --> clr-netcore[CoreCLR and CoreRT for .NET Core]
  net-clslib --> basic-clslib[.NET Standard]
  basic-clslib --> |Extension|netframework-clslib[.NET Framework Base Class Libary]
  basic-clslib --> |Extension|netcore-clslib[.NET Core base Class Libary]
  net-appframework --> asp.net[APS.NET]
  net-appframework --> windows-forms[Windows Forms]
  net-appframework --> wpf[Windows Presentation Foundation]
  net-devtools --> lang-compilers[Language Compilers]
  net-devtools --> project-file[Project File System]
  net-devtools --> net-build[NET Build Engine]
  net-devtools --> net-package[Pageake Manager]
  net-devtools --> net-opensrc[Open Source Build Orchestration]
  lang-compilers --> roslyn[Roslyn for C#]
  project-file --> csharp[.csporj]
  project-file --> vb[.vbproj]
  project-file --> fsharp[.fsproj]
  net-build --> msbuild[MSBuild]
  net-build --> clibuld[DotNet CLI]
  net-package --> nuget[NuGet]
  net-opensrc --> cake[CAKE]
  net-opensrc --> fake[FAKE]
```
